declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'-/-'
Handle `zeshy`-specific aliases.
-/-

# ....................{ TESTERS                            }....................
declare_alias_with_stdin <<'/---'
[status: boolean] is_zeshy_debug(void)

Return success if this is a *debug release* of `zeshy` (i.e., an unoptimized and
overly verbose version of `zeshy` compiled with developer-specific logic).
Specifically, return success if the current instance of `zeshy`:

* Resides in a developer-specific `git` repository.
* Was passed command-line option `--digest-debug`.
/---
if (( ZESHY_IS_DEBUG )) {
    alias is_zeshy_debug='true'
} else {
    alias is_zeshy_debug='false'
}

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
